data.name: InviteRoleHelpText
data.value:
Owners are users that have complete control over the community. They can delete the community and also remove you as a user. Add only trusted users as an Owner.
Moderators are users that have partial control over the community. They can edit the community description and contents. They may add other users as well. They cannot delete the community or remove owners.
Contributors are users that can contribute content to the community. They cannot remove other user’s content.
Readers are users that have view only access to the community. This is a useful role when you want to grant read-only acces to a community that is Private.

data.name: JoinFromInviteMessage
data.value:
Congratulations!

You have been added to this community as a {0}.

As a reader, you can view the contents of this community but not edit it.

As a contributor, you can contribute your content to this community. Simply click the “Add Content” link to start adding your own content.

As a moderator, you can manage the content and permissions of this community.

As a owner, you have complete control over the content and user permissions of this community.
